// dsshape's datasheet ILLEGALLY defines a shape. A datasheet DESCRIBES REQUIREMENTS — it states the
// components a driver must provide (`v`) and storage requirements, but never defines a shape. The
// `Box :: arche { v }` line is the violation. Support file (the error fires when a driver imports it).
// RUN: true
v   :: float;
Box :: arche { v }
[4] Box;
